<p>Restaurant inspections ensure that food served to the public at licensed food establishments follows food safety guidelines. The <strong>Food Protection Division of the Chicago Department of Public Health (CDPH)</strong> is committed to maintaining the safety of food bought, sold, or prepared for public consumption in Chicago by carrying out <code class="highlighter-rouge">science-based inspections</code> of all retail food establishments. These inspections promote <code class="highlighter-rouge">public health</code> in areas of <code class="highlighter-rouge">food safety and sanitation</code> and prevent the occurrence of food-borne illness.</p>

